<TITLE> Yuvraj Singh to undergo treatment in Australia </TITLE>
<TEXT>
 Dhaka, Feb 22 (bdnews24.com)  Indian batsman Yuvraj Singh will be off to Australia for treatment on the ligament tear he suffered on his left wrist during the tour of Bangladesh. Yuvraj sustained the injury during the second Test in Mirpur, and was subsequently ruled out of the Test and ODI series against South Africa, reports Cricinfo. "The BCCI has asked Yuvraj to go to Melbourne for consultation. But I don't know whether he has departed," Ratnakar Shetty, the Indian board's chief administrative officer, told PTI. Yuvraj had informed on his Twitter page about the decision, after India's thrilling one-run win over South Africa in the first ODI in Jaipur. "Great stuff India! Am off to Australia for treatment -- bye guys," he wrote in his Twitter 
